      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but if you look closer at the actual content, text A is basically just using big words to say the same thing as text B. isn't it kind of a stretch to say the person who wrote A is more \"capable\" if they're just using more complex words? like, would you say someone who uses AAVE actually has a lower cognitive ability in a real-world setting, or is it purely just about the \"vibe\" of the words they use?",
